# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Global vote counter backend
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Without this variable, votes are stored per-browser in localStorage only
# (visitors cannot see each other's tallies).
#
# To enable cross-visitor vote sharing:
#   1. cd workers/votes
#   2. npm install -g wrangler   (if not already installed)
#   3. wrangler login
#   4. wrangler kv namespace create VOTES
#      → copy the returned `id` into workers/votes/wrangler.toml
#   5. wrangler deploy
#   6. Copy the printed worker URL and paste it below in .env.local
#
# The worker is free on Cloudflare's free tier:
#   100,000 reads/day · 1,000 writes/day — more than enough for a portfolio.
#
VITE_VOTES_API=https://shem-votes.shemrodger.workers.dev
